// awareness_graph.proto — gRPC contract for the awareness graph service.
//
// Design rules:
//   - Briefing is the primary consumer surface. It returns prose composed
//     from SPARQL results — a single tool agents call instead of 200.
//   - Impact is the structured equivalent: same data shape as Briefing but
//     returned as typed nodes rather than narration. Used by code review
//     tools, the pre-commit guard, etc.
//   - Query is raw SPARQL passthrough — admin/debug only, RBAC-gated.
//     Not exposed to MCP tools by default; intended for the operator CLI.
//   - Resolve is a single-node lookup for following annotation IDs in code
//     (// @invariant: X) back to their full triple set.
//
// Annotation provenance:
//   When triples come from @-annotations in source code rather than from
//   a YAML file, the response carries a CodeAnchor: file path + symbol
//   (if function-scoped) + line range. This is what makes "where is this
//   rule actually enforced in code" answerable.

